{"questionId":"3018461","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>There are only <strong>three</strong> integer sets of values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math>, that form an AS-linear function.&nbsp;One of these is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>State any further restrictions on the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><mo>≠</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>≠</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"3018461","referenceCode":"23M.3.AHL.TZ2.2biii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"State any further restrictions on the value of m.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"iii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.1—Equations of straight lines, parallel and perpendicular","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.2—Functions, notation domain, range and inverse as reflection","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.2—Arithmetic sequences and series"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
